20told%20international%20news%20organisations%20Reuters%20and%20Agence%20France%20Presse%20that%20it%20cannot%20guarantee%20the%20safety%20of%20their%20journalists%20operating%20in%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%20under%20Israeli%20bombardment%20and%20siege%20for%20almost%20three%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EGaza%2C%20a%20Palestinian%20enclave%20run%20by%20the%20militant%20group%20Hamas%2C%20has%20been%20under%20bombardment%20since%20Oct.%207%20when%20Hamas%20gunmen%20burst%20through%20the%20Gaza%20border%20into%20Israel%20and%20killed%20some%201%2C400%20people.%20Gaza's%20health%20ministry%20says%20around%207%2C000%20people%20have%20been%20killed%20by%20Israeli%20strikes.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Israel%20Defense%20Forces%20wrote%20to%20Reuters%20and%20AFP%20this%20week%20after%20they%20had%20sought%20assurances%20that%20their%20journalists%20in%20Gaza%20would%20not%20be%20targeted%20by%20Israeli%20strikes.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20IDF%20is%20targeting%20all%20Hamas%20military%20activity%20throughout%20Gaza%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20IDF%20letter%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20Hamas%20deliberately%20put%20military%20operations%20%26quot%3Bin%20the%20vicinity%20of%20journalists%20and%20civilians%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20IDF%20also%20noted%20that%20its%20high-intensity%20strikes%20on%20Hamas%20targets%20could%20cause%20damage%20to%20surrounding%20buildings%20and%20that%20Hamas%20rockets%20could%20also%20misfire%20and%20kill%20people%20inside%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUnder%20these%20circumstances%2C%20we%20cannot%20guarantee%20your%20employees'%20safety%2C%20and%20strongly%20urge%20you%20to%20take%20all%20necessary%20measures%20for%20their%20safety%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20IDF%20letter%20concluded.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHamas%20did%20not%20immediately%20comment%20when%20asked%20about%20the%20IDF's%20allegation%20that%20it%20put%20military%20operations%20near%20where%20journalists%20in%20Gaza%20are%20known%20to%20be%20based.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EReuters%20could%20not%20verify%20how%20many%20other%20news%20organizations%20operating%20in%20Gaza%20had%20received%20the%20same%20letter%20from%20the%20IDF.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20IDF%20did%20not%20have%20any%20immediate%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EReuters%20and%20AFP%20said%20they%20were%20very%20concerned%20about%20the%20safety%20of%20journalists%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20situation%20on%20the%20ground%20is%20dire%2C%20and%20the%20IDF's%20unwillingness%20to%20give%20assurances%20about%20the%20safety%20of%20our%20staff%20threatens%20their%20ability%20to%20deliver%20the%20news%20about%20this%20conflict%20without%20fear%20of%20being%20injured%20or%20killed%2C%26quot%3B%20Reuters%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20in%20response%20to%20receiving%20the%20Israel%20military%20letter.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAFP%20Global%20News%20Director%20Phil%20Chetwynd%20said%20his%20news%20organisation%20had%20received%20the%20same%20letter.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20in%20an%20incredibly%20precarious%20position%20and%20it's%20important%20that%20the%20world%20understands%20that%20there%20is%20a%20large%20team%20of%20journalists%20working%20in%20extremely%20dangerous%20conditions%2C%26quot%3B%20Chetwynd%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Committee%20to%20Protect%20Journalists%20says%20at%20least%2027%20journalists%20have%20been%20killed%20since%20the%20war%20began%2C%20mostly%20in%20Gaza%20but%20also%20in%20Israel%20and%20southern%20Lebanon.%20As%20of%20October%2027%2C%20according%20to%20CPJ's%20latest%20update%2C%2022%20Palestinians%2C%20four%20Israelis%20and%20one%20Lebanese%20have%20been%20killed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698447900000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-10%2F7ndvfk08_israelgaza-war-reuters_625x300_17_October_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3