essinsider.com%2Fwhy-cruise-self-driving-robotaxis-were-banned-in-san-francisco-2023-10%5C%22%3ECalifornia's%20indefinite%20suspension%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20month%2C%20the%20National%20Highway%20Traffic%20Safety%20Administration%20announced%20that%20it%20was%C2%A0investigating%20Cruise's%20autonomous%20vehicle%20division%C2%A0after%20receiving%20reports%20of%20incidents%20where%20vehicles%20may%20not%20have%20used%20proper%20caution%20around%20pedestrians%20in%20roadways%2C%20including%20crosswalks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20NHTSA's%20Office%20of%20Defects%20Investigation%20said%20it%20received%20two%20reports%20involving%20pedestrian%20injuries%20from%20Cruise%20vehicles.%20It%20also%20identified%20two%20additional%20incidents%20from%20videos%20posted%20to%20public%20websites%2C%20noting%20that%20the%20total%20number%20is%20unknown.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20December%20of%20last%20year%2C%20the%20NHTSA%20opened%20a%20separate%20probe%20into%20reports%20of%20Cruise's%20robotaxis%20that%20stopped%20too%20quickly%20or%20unexpectedly%20quit%20moving%2C%20potentially%20stranding%20passengers.%20Three%20rear-end%20collisions%20that%20reportedly%20took%20place%20after%20Cruise%20AVs%20braked%20hard%20kicked%20off%20the%20investigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20an%20Oct.%2020%20letter%20that%20was%20made%20public%20Thursday%2C%20since%20beginning%20this%20probe%20the%20NHTSA%20has%20received%20five%20other%20reports%20of%20Cruise%20AVs%20unexpectedly%20braking%20with%20no%20obstacles%20ahead.%20Each%20case%20involved%20AVs%20operating%20without%20human%20supervision%20and%20resulted%20in%20rear-end%20collisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20welcome%20NHTSA's%20questions%20related%20to%20our%20safety%20record%20and%20operations%2C%26quot%3B%20Cruise%20spokesperson%20Hannah%20Lindow%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20sent%20to%20The%20Associated%20Press%20Friday.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20cooperated%20with%20each%20of%20their%20requests%20to%20date%20as%20part%20of%20the%20ongoing%20investigation%20process%20and%20will%20continue%20doing%20so.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECruise%20has%20previously%20maintained%20that%20its%20record%20of%20driverless%20miles%20have%20outperformed%20comparable%20human%20drivers%20in%20terms%20of%20safety%2C%20notably%20crash%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGeneral%20Motors%20Co.%2C%20which%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frobotaxis-san-francisco-cruise-waymo-autonomous-vehicles-california-2023-8%5C%22%3Eambitious%20goals%20for%20Cruise%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20has%20taken%20a%20significant%20blow%20this%20week.%20The%20Detroit%20automaker%20had%20been%20expecting%20annual%20revenue%20of%20%241%20billion%20from%20Cruise%20by%202025%20%E2%80%94%20a%20big%20jump%20from%20the%20%24106%20million%20in%20revenue%20last%20year%20when%20the%20company%20lost%20nearly%20%242%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECruise%20has%20also%20tested%20a%20robotaxi%20service%20in%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20as%20well%20as%20cities%20like%20Phoenix%20and%20Austin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20California%20Department%20of%20Motor%20Vehicles'%20didn't%20elaborate%20on%20specific%20reasons%20for%20its%20suspension%20of%20Cruise's%20license%20this%20week%2C%20the%20Tuesday%20revocation%20followed%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcruise-slashes-robotaxi-fleet-half-after-collision-incidents-san-francisco-2023-8%5C%22%3Eseries%20of%20incidents%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20heightened%20concerns%20about%20the%20hazards%20and%20inconveniences%20caused%20by%20Cruise's%20robotaxis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgm-halts-cruise-driverless-robotaxi-operations-nationwide-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698429677000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653bf4c2356802a56be6209a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgm