0of%20India's%20Hungryalist%20Movement%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F27202418%2FThe-Wire-58.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKolkata%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Poet%20and%20novelist%20Malay%20Roychoudhury%2C%20one%20of%20Bengal%E2%80%99s%20best-known%20counterculture%20icons%2C%20breathed%20his%20last%20in%20Kolkata%20on%20Thursday%2C%20October%2027.%20He%20was%2084.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20co-founder%20of%20the%20Hungry%20Generation%20aka%20Hungryalist%20movement%2C%20one%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20major%20anti-establishment%20literary%20ventures%2C%20Roychoudhury%20was%20one%20of%20Independent%20India%E2%80%99s%20earliest%20poets%20to%20have%20faced%20arrest%20and%20undergone%20trial%20on%20obscenity%20charges.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20curses%20that%20Malay%20and%20his%20friends%20spewed%20in%20their%20times%20feel%20like%20gold%20letterings%20in%20today%E2%80%99s%20times%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20writer%2C%20film%2C%20and%20literature%20critic%20Sanjoy%20Mukhopadhyay.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELaunched%20by%20Bengali%20writers%20in%20the%20early%201960s%2C%20Hungryalist%20literature%20triggered%20nationwide%20debate%20and%20influenced%20anti-establishment%20literary%20movements%20in%20Hindi%2C%20Telugu%2C%20and%20Marathi%20during%20the%20late%20%E2%80%9860s.%20His%20writings%20have%20been%20translated%20into%20several%20major%20Indian%20languages%20as%20well%20as%20English%2C%20German%2C%20French%2C%20Spanish%2C%20Russian%2C%20and%20Italian.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBorn%20in%201939%2C%20Roychoudhury%20was%20deeply%20influenced%20by%20the%20slum%20culture%20of%20Patna%E2%80%99s%20Imlitala%20ghetto%20where%20he%20and%20his%20elder%20brother%2C%20Samir%2C%20grew%20up.%20Living%20in%20a%20neighbourhood%20comprising%20%E2%80%98low%20caste%E2%80%99%20Hindus%2C%20Dalits%2C%20and%20Shia%20Muslims%2C%20Roychoudhury%20developed%20his%20literary%20vocabulary%20by%20listening%20to%20his%20neighbour%20reciting%20Ghalib%20and%20Faiz%20Ahmed%20Faiz.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELater%2C%20at%20Ram%20Mohun%20Seminary%20School%2C%20a%20student-cum-librarian%20initiated%20him%20into%20Marxism%20and%20the%20works%20of%20literary%20stalwarts%20like%20Rabindranath%20Tagore%20and%20Jibananda%20Das.%20Two%20servants%20at%20their%20Imlitala%20house%20who%20were%20well%20versed%20in%20poet%20Tulsidasa%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3ERamcharitmanas%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20%3Cem%3ERamshalaka%3C%2Fem%3E%20were%20also%20responsible%20for%20moulding%20Roychoudhury%E2%80%99s%20artistic%20sensibilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERoychoudhury%20reminisced%20about%20his%20days%20at%20Imlitala%2C%20his%20father%E2%80%99s%20photography%20studio%2C%20and%20life%20among%20the%20downtrodden%20in%20%3Cem%3EChotoloker%20Chotobela%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20memoir%20published%20by%20Charchapada%20in%202012.%20%3Cem%3EChhotolok%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20an%20antonym%20for%20%3Cem%3EBhadrolok%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Ea%20nomenclature%20used%20to%20describe%20the%20upper-caste%2C%20English-educated%20Bengali%20Hindus.%20Roychoudhury%20always%20insisted%20that%20he%20belonged%20to%20the%20domain%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3Echhotolok%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20or%20the%20subaltern.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERoychoudhury%E2%80%99s%20father%20had%20sent%20him%20away%20to%20their%20house%20in%20Patna%E2%80%99s%20Dariapur%20locality%20and%20the%20older%20brother%20Samir%20to%20Chaibasa%20(now%20in%20Jharkhand)%20so%20that%20they%20would%20escape%20Imlitala%E2%80%99s%20bad%20reputation%20of%20free%20sex%2C%20toddy%2C%20cannabis%2C%20and%20hashish.%20However%2C%20building%20a%20voice%20for%20the%20lowest%20of%20the%20low%20became%20Roychoudhury%E2%80%99s%20passion%20when%20the%20two%20brothers%20were%20confronted%20with%20the%20post-Partition%20upheaval%2C%20sectarian%20violence%2C%20and%20refugee%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20Roychoudhury%20said%20in%20a%202023%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcitylights.com%2Finterview-with-malay-roychoudhury-poet-of-hungryalism%2F%5C%22%3Einterview%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20Evan%20Kennedy%20for%20the%20New%20York-based%20City%20Lights%20Bookstore%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%C2%A0told%20my%20brother%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20raise%20our%20voice.%20We%20simple%20people%20have%20nothing%20to%20do.%20Let%E2%80%99s%20print%20leaflets%20against%20the%20government%2C%20the%20system.%20Whatever%20we%20like%2C%20we%E2%80%99ll%20write%2C%20freely.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20turbulent%201960s%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFrom%20humble%20beginnings%2C%20the%20Hungryalist%20movement%20gathered%20momentum%20when%20like-minded%20litterateurs%20like%20Shaileswar%20Ghosh%2C%20Debi%20Roy%2C%20Pradip%20Chaudhuri%2C%20Basudeb%20Dasgupta%2C%20Subhas%20Ghosh%2C%20Falguni%20Roy%2C%20and%20others%20contributed%20to%20the%20vision%20and%20created%20a%20unique%20language%20of%20insult%20and%20anger%20against%20the%20establishment.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Hungryalists%20wanted%20to%20write%20differently%20and%20create%20a%20language%20of%20the%20subaltern.%20%E2%80%9CTo%20different%20authorities%2C%20we%20had%20sent%20paper%20masks%20of%20Indian%20gods%2C%20jokers%2C%20Mickey%20Mouse%2C%20rakshasas.%20They%20were%20really%20cheap%20and%20for%20children.%20On%20the%20reverse%20we%20had%20printed%2C%20%E2%80%98Please%20remove%20your%20mask.%20From%20Hungry%20Generation.%E2%80%99%20They%20never%20thought%20that%20these%20things%20could%20come%20to%20them%2C%E2%80%9D%20Roychoudhury%20said%20in%20the%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F27202146%2Fthe-hungries.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22718%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F27202146%2Fthe-hungries.jpg%20718w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F27202146%2Fthe-hungries-300x200.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-682153%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22479%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EWriters%20of%20Hungry%20generation.%20From%20the%20top%20left%20moving%20clockwise%3A%20Saileswar%20Ghose%2C%20Malay%20Roy%20Choudhury%20and%20Subhas%20Ghose%20Basudeb%20Dasgupta%2C%20David%20Garcia%2C%20and%20Subimal%20Basak.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%2FTridib%20Mitra%2FCC%20BY-SA%203.0%20DEED.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20movement%20began%20to%20attract%20attention%20and%20create%20controversies%20from%201963%20onwards%20due%20to%20its%20ruthless%20verbiage.%20Allen%20Ginsberg%2C%20one%20of%20the%20pivotal%20figures%20of%20the%20American%20Beat%20Movement%2C%20stayed%20with%20the%20Roychoudhury%20brothers%20in%20Patna%20in%201963.%20Apart%20from%20exchanging%20literary%20notes%2C%20Ginsberg%20also%20took%20photos%20of%20Indian%20lepers%2C%20beggars%2C%20and%20refugees%2C%20which%20angered%20the%20poet%20and%20his%20father.%20Roychoudhury%20thought%20Ginsberg%20was%20seeing%20India%20through%20the%20eyes%20of%20a%20common%20white%20tourist.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESoon%20after%20Ginsberg%E2%80%99s%20departure%2C%20Roychoudhury%E2%80%99s%20dangerous%20writings%20were%20to%20change%20his%20life%20unalterably.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20his%201963%20poem%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CPrachanda%20Baidyutik%20Chhutar%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Stark%20Electric%20Jesus)%2C%20which%20prompted%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20actions%20against%20the%20Hungryalists.%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EOh%20I%E2%80%99ll%20die%20I%E2%80%99ll%20die%20I%E2%80%99ll%20die%3Cbr%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EMy%20skin%20is%20in%20blazing%20furor%3Cbr%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EI%20do%20not%20know%20what%20I%E2%80%99ll%20do%20where%20I%E2%80%99ll%20go%20oh%20I%20am%20sick%3Cbr%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EI%E2%80%99ll%20kick%20all%20the%20Arts%20in%20the%20back%20and%20go%20away%20Shubha%3Cbr%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EShubha%20let%20me%20go%20and%20live%20in%20your%20cloaked%20melon%3Cbr%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EIn%20the%20unfastened%20shadow%20of%20dark%20destroyed%20saffron%20curtain%3Cbr%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20last%20anchor%20is%20leaving%20me%20after%20I%20got%20the%20other%20anchors%20lifted%3Cbr%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EI%20can%E2%80%99t%20resist%20anymore%2C%20million%20glass-panes%20are%20breaking%20in%20my%20cortex%3Cbr%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EI%20know%2C%20Shubha%2C%20spread%20out%20your%20matrix%2C%20give%20me%20peace%3Cbr%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EEach%20vein%20is%20carrying%20a%20stream%20of%20tears%20up%20to%20the%20heart%3Cbr%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EBrain%E2%80%99s%20contagious%20flints%20are%20decomposing%20out%20of%20eternal%20sickness%3Cbr%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EMother%20why%20didn%E2%80%99t%20you%20give%20me%20birth%20in%20the%20form%20of%20a%20skeleton%3Cbr%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EI%E2%80%99d%20have%20gone%20two%20billion%20light%20years%20and%20kissed%20God%E2%80%99s%20ass%3Cbr%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EBut%20nothing%20pleases%20me%20nothing%20sounds%20well%3Cbr%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EI%20feel%20nauseated%20with%20more%20than%20a%20single%20kiss%3Cbr%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EI%E2%80%99ve%20forgotten%20women%20during%20copulation%20and%20returned%20to%20Muse%3Cbr%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EInto%20the%20sun-colored%20bladder%3Cbr%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EI%20do%20not%20know%20what%20these%20happenings%20are%20but%20they%20are%20occurring%20within%20me%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(An%20excerpt%20from%20Malay%20Roychoudhury%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9CStark%20Electric%20Jesus%2C%E2%80%9D%20as%20published%20in%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3ECity%20Lights%3Cem%3E%20Journal%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3ENumber%203%20(1966))%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20first%20Hungry%20anthology%20came%20out%20in%20March%201964%2C%20police%20picked%20up%20six%20of%20them%20in%20a%20string%20of%20arrests%20%E2%80%93%20Saileshwar%20Ghosh%20and%20Subhas%20Ghosh%20from%20Kolkata%3B%20Malay%20and%20Samir%20Roychoudhury%20from%20Patna%3B%20Pradip%20Choudhuri%20from%20Tripura%3B%20and%20Haradhan%20Dhara%20from%20Howrah.%20Malay%20alone%20underwent%20trial%20for%20%E2%80%98obscenity%E2%80%99%20in%20his%20poem%2C%20as%20the%20police%20tried%20to%20turn%20the%20other%20accused%20into%20approvers%20against%20him.%20However%2C%20most%20of%20these%20poets%20ultimately%20defended%20him%20in%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20a%20city%20sessions%20court%20in%20Kolkata%20convicted%20Roychoudhury%2C%20he%20was%20later%20acquitted%20by%20the%20Calcutta%20high%20court.%20The%20entire%20legal%20battle%20lasted%20nearly%20three%20years.%20The%20chain%20of%20events%20took%20Kolkata%E2%80%99s%20literary%20sphere%20by%20storm.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Cem%3ETime%20Magazine%20%3C%2Fem%3Ereported%20on%20the%20trial%20in%20their%20November%201964%20issue%2C%20%E2%80%9CIn%20a%20land%20that%20has%20become%20so%20straitly%20laced%20that%20its%20movie%20heroines%20must%20burst%20into%20song%20rather%20than%20be%20kissed%2C%20five%20scruffy%20young%20poets%20were%20hauled%20into%20Calcutta%E2%80%99s%20dreary%20Bankshall%20Court%20for%20publishing%20works%20that%20would%20have%20melted%20even%20Vatsyayana%E2%80%99s%20pen.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBy%201970%2C%20translations%20of%20Hungryalist%20texts%20appeared%20in%20literary%20periodicals%20from%20different%20parts%20of%20the%20world%20%E2%80%93%20Mexico%2C%20Argentina%2C%20Australia%2C%20Germany%2C%20France%2C%20the%20UK%2C%20and%20the%20US.%20Close%20to%2060%20Hungry-influenced%20magazines%20were%20published%20between%20the%201960s%20and%20%E2%80%9980s%2C%20including%20%3Cem%3EKshudhartha%20Pratirodh%3C%2Fem%3E%20(The%20Hungry%20Resistance)%2C%20%3Cem%3ESwakal%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Our%20Times)%2C%20%3Cem%3EPphoo%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Huh!)%2C%20%3Cem%3EUpadruta%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Disturbed)%2C%20%3Cem%3EZebra%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3EGiraffe%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%201965%2C%20the%20movement%20fizzled%20out%2C%20beaten%20out%20of%20shape%20and%20spirit%20by%20the%20authority%E2%80%99s%20harsh%20measures.%20For%20a%20time%2C%20Roychoudhury%20took%20up%20a%20government%20job%20at%20Agriculture%2C%20Refinance%2C%20and%20Development%20Corporation.%20On%20his%20return%20to%20literary%20life%20two%20decades%20later%2C%20he%20won%20and%20declined%20the%20Sahitya%20Academic%20Award%20for%20translating%20Dharamvir%20Bharati%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3ESuraj%20Ka%20Satwan%20Ghora%20%3C%2Fem%3Einto%20Bengali.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%201995%2C%20Roychoudhury%E2%80%99s%20literary%20career%20took%20a%20dramatic%20turn%20as%20he%20introduced%20his%20%3Cem%3EAdhunantika%20%3C%2Fem%3Ephase%20(%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EAdhu%E2%80%99%20%3C%2Fem%3Emeaning%20%E2%80%9Cnew%E2%80%9D%3B%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3ENantik%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fem%3Emeaning%20%E2%80%98end%E2%80%99)%20where%20he%20became%20one%20of%20Bengali%20literature%E2%80%99s%20pioneering%20voices%20in%20the%20post-modernist%20writing%20style.%20His%20poetry%20collections%20from%20this%20phase%20are%C2%A0%3Cem%3EChitkar%20Samagra%2C%20Chhatrakhan%2C%20Ja%20Lagbey%20Bolben%2C%20Atmadhangser%20Sahasrabda%2C%20Postmodern%20Ahlader%20Kobita%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%C2%A0%3Cem%3EKounaper%20Luchimangso%3C%2Fem%3E.%20His%20novels%20from%20the%20period%20include%C2%A0%3Cem%3ENamgandho%2C%20Jalanjali%2C%20Nakhadanta%2C%20Ei%20Adham%20Oi%20Adham%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%C2%A0%3Cem%3EArup%20Tomar%20Entokanta%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20some%20lines%20from%20%3Cem%3EBlood%20Lyric%20%3C%2Fem%3Epublished%20in%202011%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CWhat%20have%20I%20done%20for%20poetry%20plunging%20into%C2%A0%20lava-spewing%20volcano%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cbr%3E%20What%20are%20these%3F%20What%20are%20these%3F%20Result%20of%20searches%20at%20home%3Cbr%3E%20of%20Poetry%3F%20Bromide%20sepia%20babies%20from%20Dad%E2%80%99s%20broken%20almirah%3Cbr%3E%20of%20Poetry!%20Mom%E2%80%99s%20Benares%20sari%20torn%20out%20of%20hammered%20box%3Cbr%3E%20of%20Poetry!%20Breaths%20are%20recorded%20in%20the%20seizure%20list%3Cbr%3E%20of%20Poetry!%20Show%20me%20show%20me%20what%20else%20is%20coming%20out%3Cbr%3E%20of%20Poetry!%20Shame%20on%20you%3B%20girl%E2%80%99s%20half-licked%20guy!%20Die%20you%20die%3Cbr%3E%20of%20Poetry!%20Wave%20piercing%20sharks%20chew%20up%20flesh%20%26amp%3B%20bone%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ERoychoudhury%20continued%20to%20be%20active%20on%20the%20Bengali%20literary%20circuit%2C%20with%20books%20and%20writings%20being%20released%20regularly%20in%20the%20Kolkata%20Book%20Fair%20and%20the%20Little%20Magazine%20Fair.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20news%20of%20his%20death%20broke%2C%20the%20little%20magazine%20fraternity%20of%20Bengal%2C%20India%2C%20and%20abroad%20took%20to%20social%20media%20in%20hoards%20to%20express%20their%20condolences.%20Many%20lamented%20his%20loss.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHis%20impact%20and%20influence%20over%20India%E2%80%99s%20counter-establishment%20scenario%20were%20beautifully%20summed%20up%20by%20the%20late%20American%20writer-scholar%20Howard%20McCord%3A%20%E2%80%9CMalay%20Roy%20Choudhury%2C%20a%20Bengali%20poet%2C%20has%20been%20a%20central%20figure%20in%20the%20Hungry%20Generation%E2%80%99s%20attack%20on%20the%20Indian%20cultural%20establishment%20since%20the%20movement%20began%20in%20the%20early%201960s.%20%E2%80%A6Acid%2C%20destructive%2C%20morbid%2C%20nihilistic%2C%20outrageous%2C%20mad%2C%20hallucinatory%2C%20shrill%20%E2%80%93%20these%20characterise%20the%20terrifying%20and%20cleansing%20visions%E2%80%9D%20that%20%E2%80%9CIndian%20literature%20must%20endure%20if%20it%20is%20to%20be%20vital%20again.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMalay%20Roychoudhury%20is%20survived%20by%20his%20wife%20Shalila%20Roychoudhury%2C%20his%20daughter%20Anushree%20Prashant%2C%20son%20Jitendra%20and%20two%20grandchildren.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESreemanti%20Sengupta%20is%20a%20Kolkata-based%20freelance%20writer%2C%20poet%2C%20and%20media%20studies%20lecturer.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698418721000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F27202418%2FThe-Wire-58.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fculture%2Fmalay-roychoudhury-1939-2023-the-explosive-poet-of-indias-hungryalist-movement%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Malay%20Roychoudhury%2C%20one%20of%20the%20co-founders%20of%20the%201960s'%20Hungryalist%20literary%20movement%2C%20was%20a%20notorious%20cocktail%20of%20confessional%20verse%20that%20continually%20flouted%20norms%20and%20flirted%20with%20danger.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fculture%2Fmalay-roychoudhury-1939-2023-the-explosive-poet-of-indias-hungryalist-movement%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bela%20bill%3A%20South%20Africans%20face%20jail%20if%20children%20not%20in%20school%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698417994000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F112DC%2Fproduction%2F_131546307_schoolchildsa.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-africa-67231637%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Parliament%20passes%20the%20biggest%20education%20reform%20since%20the%20end%20of%20apartheid%20in%201994.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A48%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-africa-67231637%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-africa-67231637.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-africa-67231637.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Raj%20on%20being%20called%20'porn%20king'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698417500000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-104761272%2Cimgsize-33278.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fent