C2%A0Charles%20Taylor%20and%20Michael%20Waltzer%2C%20the%20prodigious%20Marxist%20Perry%20Anderson%20and%20our%20very%20own%20Natalie%20Zemon%20Davis.%20These%20distinguished%20scholars%20%C2%A0were%20to%20stay%20in%20our%20city%20for%20a%20week%20interacting%20with%20the%20Delhi%20audiences.%20But%20those%2C%20as%20they%20say%2C%20were%20different%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EReturning%20once%20more%20to%20the%20sorely%20missed%20late%20Natalie%20Davis%E2%80%A6%20Several%20years%20ago%2C%20a%20French%20scholar%20had%20this%20to%20say%20about%20interdisciplinary%20work%20in%20the%20humanities%20and%20the%20social%20sciences%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CInterdisciplinary%20work%2C%20so%20much%20discussed%20these%20days%2C%20is%20not%20about%20confronting%20already%20constituted%20disciplines%20(none%20of%20which%2C%20is%20in%20fact%2C%20willing%20to%20let%20go%20of%20itself).%20To%20do%20something%20interdisciplinary%20it%20is%20not%20enough%20to%20choose%20a%20%E2%80%9Csubject%E2%80%9D%20(a%20theme)%20and%20gather%20around%20it%20two%20or%20three%20sciences.%20Interdisciplinarity%20consists%20in%20creating%20a%20new%20object%20that%20belongs%20to%20no%20one.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDavis%20is%20widely%20regarded%20by%20scholars%20throughout%20the%20world%20as%20a%20historian%20who%20has%20created%20several%20such%20new%20%E2%80%98objects%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20did%20not%20%3Cem%3Ebelong%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20anyone%20%E2%80%93%20indeed%20not%20regarded%20as%20objects%20at%20all%2C%20till%20she%20dared%20to%20write%20these%20(peoples)%20anew.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EForty%20years%20ago%2C%20someone%20who%20no%20doubt%20knew%20Davis%20well%20described%20her%20in%20an%20%3Cem%3EEnvoi%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20commendatory%20remarks%20at%20the%20end%20of%20her%20%3Cem%3ESociety%20and%20Culture%20in%20Early%20Modern%20France%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20these%20lines%2C%20which%20have%20gained%20in%20poignancy%20with%20every%20new%20book%20she%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBorn%20abroad%2C%20she%20longs%20for%20you%20%3Cem%3Ecampagnons%3Cbr%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3EShe%20longs%20to%20shake%20your%20hand%2C%20to%20share%20your%20wine%2C%3Cbr%3E%20Through%20the%20pane%20she%20hears%20you%20but%20is%20not%20heard%2C%3Cbr%3E%20She%20deserves%20your%20pity%20but%20will%20not%20have%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20songs%20you%20think%20are%20vanished%20once%20they%20are%20sung%2C%3Cbr%3E%20The%20pleas%20you%20think%20are%20wasted%20if%20turned%20down%2C%3Cbr%3E%20Jokes%20you%20dismiss%20if%20no%20one%20laughs%20or%20winces%2C%3Cbr%3E%20She%20listens%20for.%20You%20speak%20sometimes%20too%20soft.%3Cbr%3E%20And%20since%20there%20is%20no%20God%2C%20she%20notes%20your%20prayers.%3Cbr%3E%20And%20since%20there%20is%20no%20God%2C%20she%20marks%20your%20fall.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERIP%20Natalie.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fshahid-amin%5C%22%3EShahid%20Amin%3C%2Fa%3E%20taught%20history%20at%20Delhi%20University%2C%201985-2015.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698404411000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F27153705%2Fnzd.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Facross-fields-and-disciplines-historian-natalie-daviss-pathbreaking-work-has-left-a-lasting-mark%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Davis%20was%20one%20of%20the%20most%20daring%20band%20of%20historians%20of%20our%20times.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A115%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Facross-fields-and-disciplines-historian-natalie-daviss-pathbreaking-work-has-left-a-lasting-mark%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20Happens%20After%20Israel%20Loses%20Its%20War%20in%20Gaza%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F12154036%2FF8Okg4HW8AAKm24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20easiest%20way%20to%20lose%20a%20war%20is%20to%20set%20impossible%20or%20contradictory%20goals.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20remaking%20the%20Middle%20East%20by%20invading%20and%20remaking%20Iraq%20into%20a%20democratic%20state%20aligned%20with%20the%20United%20States%20was%20a%20delusional%20goal%20%E2%80%93%20one%20whose%20failure%20can%20be%20seen%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nbcnews.com%2Fnews%2Fworld%2Fmassive-protests-seen-us-embassies-several-countries-gaza-hospital-bom-rcna121412%5C%22%3Emassive%20protests%20in%20front%20of%20the%20US%20embassy%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Baghdad%2C%20and%20the%20targeting%20of%20US%20personnel%20there.%20As%20Von%20Clausewitz%20noted%20so%20long%20ago%2C%20%E2%80%9CWar%20is%20the%20continuation%20of%20policy%20with%20other%20means.%E2%80%9D%20If%20the%20policy%20goals%20are%20not%20achieved%2C%20all%20military%20victory%20is%20hollow.%20The%20US%20military%20won%20every%20military%20conflict%20during%20the%20longest%20modern%20war%20it%20has%20ever%20conducted%20in%20Afghanistan%2C%20but%20it%20left%20the%20Taliban%20in%20control%20when%20it%20left.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThree%20goals%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIsrael%20has%20set%20three%20goals%20in%20its%20current%20war%2C%20two%20explicit%2C%20and%20one%20implicit%2C%20and%20it%20is%20unlikely%20to%20achieve%20them%20despite%20comprehensive%20military%2C%20economic%2C%20and%20diplomatic%20superiority.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20explicit%20goals%20are%20the%20release%20of%20civilian%20hostages%20and%20military%20prisoners%20of%20war%20(POWs)%20captured%20by%20Hamas%20in%20its%20October%207%20attacks%2C%20and%20the%20elimination%20of%20Hamas%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20implicit%20goal%20is%20to%20reinforce%20deterrence%20against%20any%20future%20attacks%2C%20so%20that%20its%20population%20feels%20secure%20after%20the%20single%20largest%20slaughter%20of%20Israeli%20civilians%20in%20the%20history%20of%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20goal%20of%20releasing%20civilians%20and%20POWs%20is%20explicitly%20at%20odds%20with%20the%20elimination%20of%20Hamas.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20hostages%20to%20be%20released%20have%20been%20four%20civilians%20after%20negotiations%20with%20Hamas%20led%20by%20Qatar.%20By%20definition%2C%20any%20further%20releases%20would%20require%20negotiations%20with%20Hamas%2C%20and%20thus%20the%20survival%20of%20the%20militant%20group%20itself.%20But%20if%20Israel%20is%20committed%20to%20eliminating%20Hamas%2C%20why%20should%20Hamas%20release%20hostages%3F%20What%20incentive%20is%20there%3F%20One%20way%20that%20Israel%20seems%20to%20be%20approaching%20squaring%20this%20circle%20is%20by%20offering%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2Foct%2F24%2Fisrael-drops-leaflets-in-gaza-offering-reward-for-hostage-information%5C%22%3Ecash%20and%20security%20rewards%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20residents%20of%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20to%20give%20information%20about%20the%20civilians%20and%20POWs%20kept%20by%20Hamas.%20Maybe%20Israel%20believes%20that%20the%20incentive%2C%20along%20with%20the%20immense%20misery%20that%20it%20has%20inflicted%20on%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20will%20be%20enough%20for%20people%20to%20turn%20against%20Hamas.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAgain%2C%20though%2C%20these%20approaches%20are%20at%20odds%20with%20each%20other.%20The%20residents%20of%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20may%20blame%20Hamas%20for%20triggering%20off%20the%20latest%20round%20of%20violence%2C%20but%20the%20bombs%20killing%20them%20are%20Israeli%20ones.%20And%20Hamas%20has%20already%20stated%20that%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20intense%20bombing%20campaign%20has%20led%20to%20the%20death%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.al-monitor.com%2Foriginals%2F2023%2F10%2Feu-urges-corridors-and-pauses-un-warns-nowhere-safe-gaza%5C%22%3Ealmost%2050%20of%20the%20224%20civilians%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20POWs%20it%20captured%2C%20as%20well%20as%20over%207%2C000%20Palestinians%2C%20overwhelmingly%20civilians%2C%20that%20have%20been%20killed.%20This%20claim%20cannot%20be%20verified%2C%20but%20given%20that%20the%20Israeli%20Defence%20Forces%20spokesperson%2C%20Daniel%20Hagari%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2Foct%2F10%2Fright-now-it-is-one-day-at-a-time-life-on-israels-frontline-with-gaza%5C%22%3Eexplicitly%20stated%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20emphasis%20of%20the%20IDF%20bombing%20campaign%20was%20%E2%80%9Con%20damage%20and%20not%20on%20accuracy%E2%80%9D%2C%20it%20is%20highly%20likely%20that%20at%20least%20some%20of%20the%20224%20will%20not%20have%20survived%20the%20bombing.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fsix-takeaways-from-the-israel-palestine-conflict%5C%22%3ESix%20Takeaways%20From%20the%20Israel-Palestine%20Conflict%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMounting%20challenges%20for%20Israel%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20intense%20bombing%20campaign%20has%20also%20made%20the%20challenge%20of%20eliminating%20Hamas%20much%20more%20difficult.%20To%20some%20degree%2C%20the%20scale%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.al-monitor.com%2Foriginals%2F2023%2F10%2Fisrael-hamas-military-balance-0%5C%22%3EIsrael%E2%80%99s%20military%20superiority%3C%2Fa%3E%20works%20against%20it.%20The%20IDF%20has%20over%20150%2C000%20regular%20troops%2C%20with%20an%20additional%20400%2C000%20reservists.%20It%20has%20total%20air%20superiority%20and%20controls%20all%20routes%20in%20and%20out%20of%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20%E2%80%93%20except%20the%20Rafah%20crossing%20which%20is%20managed%20by%20Egypt%20in%20cooperation%20with%20Israel%20and%20the%20US.%20It%20has%20one%20of%20the%20most%20sophisticated%20militaries%20on%20the%20planet.%20In%20contrast%2C%20Hamas%20militants%20number%20somewhere%20between%2010%2C000-40%2C000%20largely%20armed%20with%20assault%20rifles%20and%20rockets%20either%20smuggled%20in%20or%20fabricated%20in%20the%20Gaza%20Strip.%20As%20fighting%20forces%2C%20there%20is%20no%20comparison.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20given%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20attack%20on%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20has%20included%20attacks%20on%20everything%20including%20mosques%2C%20churches%20and%20allegedly%20even%20hospitals%20%E2%80%93%20the%20precise%20cause%20of%20the%20horrific%20blast%20at%20Al%20Ahli%20hospital%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2F2023%2F10%2F23%2F1208061552%2Fwhat-new-analysis-shows-about-the-gaza-hospital-explosion%5C%22%3Eremains%20unclear%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20the%20thousands%20killed%20are%20civilians.%20And%20since%20almost%20half%20the%20population%20of%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20is%20under%20the%20age%20of%2018%2C%20almost%20half%20of%20the%20dead%20are%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20scale%20of%20the%20suffering%20is%20such%20that%20Turkish%20President%20Erdogan%2C%20who%20had%20been%20trying%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.al-monitor.com%2Foriginals%2F2023%2F09%2Fisrael-turkey-leaders-discuss-saudi-normalization-first-new-york-meeting%5C%22%3Enormalise%20relations%20with%20Israel%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20recently%20as%20a%20meeting%20at%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20UN%20General%20Assembly%20in%20end%20September%2C%20has%20now%20called%20Hamas%20a%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fturkeys-erdogan-says-hamas-is-not-terrorist-organisation-2023-10-25%2F%5C%22%3Eliberation%20organisation%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%2C%20not%20a%20terrorist%20organisation.%20And%20a%20Hamas%20delegation%20has%20just%20arrived%20in%20Russia%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2Foct%2F26%2Fhamas-delegation-travels-to-moscow-for-talks-on-foreign-hostages-in-gaza%5C%22%3Efor%20talks%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Despite%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thenationalnews.com%2Fmena%2Fpalestine-israel%2F2023%2F10%2F24%2Fmacrons-proposal-to-fight-hamas-with-anti-isis-coalition-not-practical-experts-say%2F%5C%22%3Echildish%